article.headline: Princeton 52, Brown 37
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Noah Savage scored a career-high 23 points to lead Princeton to a 52-37 win over Brown in an Ivy League matchup on Saturday night. Scott Greenman and Luke Owings each added nine points for the Tigers (5-12, 3-1), while Owings also had a game-high four assists. Damon Huffman had 14 points and four rebounds for Brown (6-13, 2-4), which had a horrid night from the floor, hitting just 25.7 percent of its shots and going 1-for-12 from 3-point range. Mark MacDonald added eight points and six rebounds for the Bears. The Tigers quickly took control of the game, hitting 52 percent of their shots in the first half to take a 30-12 lead at the break. Brown tried to rally in the second half, but were frequently frustrated by the Tigers defense that forced 15 turnovers overall.
